article.headline: Jackson St. 57, Southern U. 46
article.story: BATON ROUGE, La. -- De'Suan Dixon scored 16 points and grabbed 15 rebounds and Jackson State beat Southern University 57-46 on Monday night. Garrison Johnson added 16 points for the Tigers (5-10, 3-0 Southwestern Athletic Conference), who won for the fifth straight time after opening the season on a 10-game losing streak. After trailing by eight points in the first half the Tigers tied the game on a layup by Hanson at 35-35 with 14:04 remaining in the game, then outscored the Jaguars 22-11 the rest of the way. Leading 49-46 with 6:22 to play, the Tigers went on an 8-0 run to seal the win. The Tigers did not hit a field goal in the final four minutes, going 4-for-8 from the foul line to extend the lead. Doug Scott lead the Jaguars (3-13, 1-3) with 12 points.
